he \u201cegocentric\u201d perception has impacted crew work. The facts we have are that C makes correct decisions quickly, has excellent attention skills, puts concern for others above everything, creates a positive atmosphere with the crew, but also has difficulty communicating ideas, is regarded as egocentric, and is not very willing to further his education.\n4. **Candidate\u202fD \u2013 leadership experience and consequences of moodiness/loner behavior:**\n   The information includes D\u2019s strong problem\u2011solving, concentration, responsibility, and ability to respond to unexpected events, together with negative traits: moody, regarded as a loner, arrogant, and relatively weak leadership. No specific examples of D\u2019s past command experience or observed effects of moodiness/loneliness on crew coordination during long flights are present.\nGiven the current evidence, **Candidate\u202fB** still appears to best combine the essential attributes of reliability, calmness under pressure, technical competence, and sound decision\u2011making for international long\u2011haul operations. The interpersonal style concerns, while real, seem manageable compared with the more substantive gaps in reliability, teamwork, or leadership observed for the other candidates.\nIf any of the other agents have additional positive information on Candidates\u202fA,\u202fC, or\u202fD\u2014particularly regarding reliability records, concrete leadership examples, or evidence that their interpersonal drawbacks do not impair crew performance\u2014please share it so we can reassess if needed.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce final answer as agent_2, not agent_3. The last user says \"Handle the requests as specified in the System Instruction.\" The system instruction says we must output PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with agent name \"agent_2\". We need to incorporate the discussion. We have already drafted a public message as agent_3. Now we need to produce as agent_2. We should consider the current state: Agent 1 and Agent 3 have both posted messages asking for more info. Agent 2 now should respond, possibly answer some of the questions if we have info, or ask further. According to the shared mental model, we have the same info as others. So we can answer that we lack specific data for those questions. We can reaffirm candidate B as best. Also we can ask if any other agents have additional info on A's reliability, D's leadership, C's communication. Provide reasoning. Then vote.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing assessment, answer the four questions (we have no additional info), ask for any missing info, reaffirm vote B. Then METADATA_JSON with vote Candidate B.\n\nProceed."}
